read_power_intent(25.10)                              read_power_intent(25.10)

Name
       read_power_intent - Reads-in power intent file and do syntax check

Syntax
       read_power_intent

       [-help]

       <fileName>

       {-cpf | -1801 | -msvDB }

       Reads-in power intent file and do syntax check. The method supports in-
       cremental  refinement  of  power intent specifications required for IP-
       based design flows.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each read_power_intent parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man read_power_intent

       <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the power intent file to be read.

       -cpf   Specifies that the CPF format power intent file will be used.

       -1801  Specifies that the IEEE1801 format power  intent  file  will  be
              used.

       -msvDB Specifies  that  the  IEEE1801 data format (.cpfdb) power intent
              file will be used.

              Note: -msvDB is for partition flow and must be  read  for  power
              intent in partition implementation.

Related Information
              * commit_power_intent

              * free_power_intent

              * write_power_intent

              * Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

